Simulate two datasets

set.seed(1)
n_samp=250

sim_df_const = 
  tibble(x=rnorm(n_samp,1,1),
  error = rnorm(n_samp,0,1),
  y = 2+3*x+error
  )

sim_df_nonconst = 
  sim_df_const |> 
  mutate(
    error = .75 *error*x,      #changing error, building in that error dist depends on x, violating regression rules
    y = 2+3*x+error
  )

Visualize

sim_df_const |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=x, y=y))+
  geom_point() 

sim_df_nonconst |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=x, y=y))+
  geom_point()

Write a function to draw a bootstrap sample.

boot_sample = function(df)
  sample_frac(df, size=1, replace = TRUE)

Does this work?

sim_df_nonconst |> 
  boot_sample() |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=x, y=y))+
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se=FALSE) +
  xlim(c(-2,4))+
  ylim(c(-5,16))
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

So I want to formalize this and extract results

boot_straps = #drawing a bootstrap sample
  tibble(iter = 1:5000) |> 
  mutate(
    bootstrap_sample = map(iter, \(i) boot_sample(df = sim_df_nonconst))
  )

Actually run my analyses

bootstrap_results = #fitting 5000 models and 5000 regressions
  boot_straps |> 
  mutate(
    fits = map(bootstrap_sample, \(df) lm(y ~ x, data = df)),
    results = map(fits, broom::tidy)
  )

Look at my results

bootstrap_results |> 
  select(iter, results) |> 
  unnest(results) |> 
  group_by(term) |> 
  summarize(
    estimate = mean(estimate),
    se = sd(estimate)
  )
## # A tibble: 2  3

Do it again but faster this time

bootstrap_results = 
sim_df_nonconst |> 
  bootstrap(n = 5000) |> 
  mutate(
    df = map(strap, as_tibble),
    fits = map(df, \(df) lm(y ~ x, data = df)),
    results = map(fits, broom::tidy)
  ) |> 
  select(.id, results) |> 
  unnest(results)

Airbnb

data("nyc_airbnb")

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb |> 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2) |> 
  rename(
    borough = neighbourhood_group
  ) |> 
  filter(
    borough != "Staten Island"
  ) |> 
  drop_na(price, stars, room_type) |> 
  select(price, stars, room_type, borough)

What this looks like

nyc_airbnb |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=stars, y=price, color=room_type)) +
  geom_point(alpha=0.5)

Try to bootstrap

airbnb_bootstrap_results = 
  nyc_airbnb |> 
  filter(borough=="Manhattan") |> 
  bootstrap(n=1000) |> 
  mutate(
    df=map(strap, as_tibble),
    fits = map(df, \(df) lm(price~stars+room_type, data=df)),
    results = map(fits, broom::tidy)
  ) |> 
  select(.id, results) |> 
  unnest(results)

Look at dist of slope for stars

airbnb_bootstrap_results |> 
  filter(term=="stars") |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=estimate))+
  geom_density()
